1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bf4 c5 4. e3
{ White's main response, protecting his d4-pawn. } 4... Nc6 5. c3
{ Although  5.c3  is the mainline , it is inaccurate.  5.Nbd2  is stronger. }
5... Qb6
{ Seizing the initiative ! Black threatens to take the b2-pawn. White can't afford to sac it because Black would be able to play ...Qxc3 afterward  (picking up a second pawn)  and return home with ...Qa5-d8. }
