{ Gaining space and forcing White to make a decision regarding his queen. } 7.
Qc2 Bf5
{ Gaining a tempo. The tactical justification is that Qxf5 loses to ...Qxb2, picking up the a1-rook. }
8. Qxf5 { Tactically unsound.  8.Qc1  is stronger. } 8... Qxb2
{ Black will play ...Qxa1 with a winning position. However, there is still room for error; if Black plays ...Qxa1 right away, White will trap Black's queen with Qc2. Black should play ...e6  (or ...g6)  to chase Qf5 away from the c2-square before taking the rook. }
