6. Bb5 cxd4
{ Black prevents dxc5 and forces White to recapture on d4. If Black had played ...Qb6 followed by ...cxd4, White could have sacrificed this pawn favorably.   6...Qb6  7.c4 !  is annoying and White can meet  7...cxd4   7...e6  would be fine for Black if it weren't for  8.a4 !  and  8...a6  can be met by  9.a5  Qa7  10.Bxc6+  , where White has a lead in development and the position is opening up.  with  8.O-O  and has excellent compensation for the pawn. }
7. exd4 Qb6
{ Black is fighting for the initiative on the queenside and c4 is less dangerous with the d4-pawn loose.   8.c4  dxc4  White has an isolated queen pawn and  9.a4  can be met with  9...Bd3   or  9...e6  10.Nxc4  Bb4+. }
