{ White's main response, protecting his d4-pawn. } 4... Nc6 5. Nbd2
{ The most accurate move order, avoiding the 5.c3 Qb6 lines.   The idea is that  5...Qb6  can be met by  6.dxc5 !  where after  ...Qxb2  there is no pawn hanging on  c3  and White has the option of playing  c4. }
